claim.claim-text:
An apparatus comprising:
an optical signal source (214) configured to generate an optical signal (222);
an optical signal detector system (216) configured to detect the optical signal (222);
a switching system (218) configured to direct the optical signal (222) from the optical signal source (214) to inputs (208) in an optical coupler (202) and direct the optical signal (222) from outputs (210) in the optical coupler (202) to the optical signal detector system (216); and
a controller (220) configured to automatically control the switching system (218) to select the inputs (208) in the optical coupler (202) for transmission of the optical signal (222) into the optical coupler (202), select the outputs (210) in the optical coupler (202) for measuring the optical signal (222) output from the optical coupler (202), and measure the optical signal (222) from the outputs (210) selected to form measurements (233).

A method for testing an optical coupler (202), the method comprising:
connecting inputs (208) of the optical coupler (202) to output ports (828) of an optical signal source (214);
connecting outputs (210) of the optical coupler (202) to input ports (840) for an optical signal detector system (216);
measuring optical signals sent through combinations of the inputs (208) and the outputs (210) of the optical coupler (202) using a switching system (218) controlled by a controller (220) to form measurements (233) of the optical signals.
